(33, 1, '2022-04-29 02:58:48', '2022-04-29 02:58:48', '<h2><strong><span>About Australian beef tenderloin</span></strong></h2>\r\n<span>Striploin, also known as Australian beef tenderloin, is the meat located on the back of the cow, along the sides of the back spine, where the cow is most sedentary. From the position it can be seen that this is tender meat, and in this part of the meat is surrounded by a layer of fat, which is the type of meat used to prepare many dishes with a high-class menu. For example, Steak, grilled, hot pot, stir-fried or pan-fried dishes…. And typically the famous beef steak.</span>\r\n\r\n<strong><span>Striploin Australian beef tenderloin </span></strong><span>has 2 classifications. Specifically, if the T-bone is left whole with an attached tenderloin, then this beef tenderloin is called a T-bone steak, or porterhouse steak.</span>\r\n\r\n<span>This is also a very common part of making famous T-bone steaks. Because the T-bone steak consists of 2 pieces of different sizes on both sides of the bone. While the smaller portion is the head of the tenderloin (tenderloin), or filet mignon, the softest part of the beef, the larger portion is part of the tenderloin.</span>\r\n\r\n<span>Believe me, once you have tasted the T-bone steak made with </span><strong><span>Australian beef tenderloin </span></strong><span>, you will not be able to forget how delicious it is.</span>', 'Thit bo', '<span>The 1.5cm Australian beef tenderloin cuts are the perfect choice for beefsteak. </span><span>With the outer fat border, the Australian beef tenderloin brings a fatty flavor, the beef will not dry out when preparing delicious dishes.</span>', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'thit-bo', '', '', '2022-04-29 02:58:48', '2022-04-29 02:58:48', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?post_type=product&#038;p=33', 0, 'product', '', 0),
